Posts.Content: Jan 14, 2013 11:30AM austingirl2013 wrote: I also got a call back in late November, my first after having mammograms for eleven years.  I worried with little sleep for five days.  I was scheduled for a mammo and an ultrasound.  After taking the spot compression images, the tech went to confer with the radiologist and she came back in and told me it was only a shadow on the first mammo and I didn't need the ultrasound.  So, yes, a lot of times it turns our to be nothing.  So hard to do, but don't worry until there is actually something confirmed to worry about!
